# SS AI Server

AI backend for WordPress image similarity search.

## Deploy to Render

1. Push this repo to GitHub
2. Go to https://dashboard.render.com/ → New Web Service
3. Connect your GitHub repo
4. Render auto-detects `render.yaml`
5. Click Create Web Service

The API will be available at `https://your-app.onrender.com`.

### Detailed Render checklist

- Ensure `render.yaml` is present at the repository root and `runtime: docker` is set (this project includes a Dockerfile).
- Confirm required secrets and environment variables are configured in Render (the `SECRET_KEY` is autogenerated by `render.yaml` but you may override it).
- If you need persistent storage for the FAISS index, confirm the `disk` entry in `render.yaml` has sufficient `sizeGB` (default: 4GB).
- If you hit build errors for native packages (faiss/torch/open-clip), check the Render Build Logs for missing system packages and adjust the `Dockerfile` to install them.

### Quick local-to-Render workflow

1. Create a feature branch and work locally:

```bash
git checkout -b feature/local-dev
python3.11 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -e ".[dev]"
cp .env.example .env
# edit .env as needed
```

2. Build and smoke-test Docker locally (optional):

```bash
docker build -t ss-ai-server:local .
docker run --rm -p 8000:8000 \
	-e PORT=8000 \
	-e ENVIRONMENT=production \
	-e WORKERS=1 \
	-e SECRET_KEY="change-me" \
	ss-ai-server:local
# then curl http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health
```

3. Push branch and open a PR, merge to `main` and Render will auto-deploy (if `autoDeploy: true`).

### Troubleshooting hints

- Build failures: copy the last 40–80 lines from Render Build Logs and inspect for pip/apt errors.
- Runtime failures: copy the uvicorn traceback from Deploy logs.
- FAISS / torch issues: ensure the `Dockerfile` installs required system libs (see Dockerfile for `libopenblas-dev`, `libgomp1`, and `libjpeg-dev`).


## Local Development

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
uvicorn ss_ai_server.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/v1/health` | Health check |
| POST | `/api/v1/search/image` | Search by image |
| POST | `/api/v1/index/product` | Index a product |
| POST | `/api/v1/index/batch` | Batch index products |
| DELETE | `/api/v1/index/product/{id}` | Delete product embeddings |
| GET | `/api/v1/admin/stats` | System stats |

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|----------|---------|-------------|
| ENVIRONMENT | development | production or development |
| SECRET_KEY | - | Set in production |
| VECTOR_STORE_PATH | /data/vector_store | FAISS index path |

See `.env.example` for all options.
